# Styling stack

**Tailwind 4 + tailwindcss-primeui** — utilities in section templates, not custom CSS classes.

## Own components (sections, custom widgets)

- Style in `.html` with Tailwind utilities (`flex`, `text-color`, `border-surface`, `rounded-border`, etc.)
- Match sibling sections (`bottleneck`, `schedule`, `mobile-header`) before inventing patterns
- Do **not** add BEM blocks to `styles.css` for custom components
- Dynamic display state → `[class.hidden]`, `ngClass`, or component `styles` only when utilities cannot express it (e.g. dynamic `color-mix`)

## PrimeNG

- Prefer component APIs and `styleClass` / `panelStyleClass` with Tailwind classes on the root
- Global `.p-*` overrides in `styles.css` only where PrimeNG owns internal DOM and passThrough is insufficient
- Check PrimeNG 21 docs before writing custom selectors

## styles.css allowed for

- `@layer base` (fonts, root tokens, `app-root` overflow)
- PrimeNG / third-party DOM overrides
- Shared utilities used across sections (`dashboard-scroll-x`, `.text-accent`) when repeated Tailwind is noisy
- Documented exceptions: Chart.js config (TS), funnel dynamic bar vars (inline component styles)

## Before styling work

1. Read an existing section template in the same area
2. Confirm whether the target is own markup (Tailwind) or PrimeNG internals (minimal global CSS)
